              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>Let me premise by saying the<lb/> present condition of both Kabals<lb/> educationally\n                considered is deplora<lb/>-ble, at least in the light of the<lb/> advanced progress\n                of the Age.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now it is proposed by the zealots<lb/> to build a new\n                Synagogue—first<lb/> disposing of one or both of the<lb/> existing structures &amp;\n                have its<lb/> interior constructed for family<lb/> pews—for male &amp; female—to\n                adopt<lb/> a new minhag—engage a reform<lb/> preacher &amp; in a word go the\n                whole<lb/> figure <hi rend=\"underline\">a la <persName>Dr Wise</persName></hi>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">In the limits of a letter I cannot<lb/> give you an adequate idea of\n                the<lb/> wishes &amp; intentions of the so called<lb/> reformers. Let me say that\n                a<lb/> very large number if not quite<lb/> a majority of the members of<lb/> both\n                societies are ready &amp; anxious</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
