                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>to adopt these views &amp; projects<lb/> unless speedily enlightened as to<lb/> their\n                apostasy. The only saving<lb/> clause to us for I class myself<lb/> among those who\n                will resist<lb/> to the utmost this wholesale<lb/>\n                <del>ann</del> system of innovation to<lb/> use no harsher term—is that<lb/> if a\n                majority of both societies<lb/> determine to adopt these doc-<lb/>-trines we can\n                restrain them<lb/> from selling the property as we<lb/> own &amp; possess in good\n                title<lb/> seats <hi rend=\"underline\">forever</hi> in the respective buildings &amp;\n                they do not propose<lb/> to allow us for these any com-<lb/>pensation or return\n                either whole<lb/> or in part in the new edifice.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have looked up the legal<lb/> authorities on this point\n                besides<lb/> taking the benefit of counsel.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
