          "rendering": [
            {
              "@id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/assets/4a09babb-018a-47a3-94f3-cd6713f35a53/original",
              "label": "Original File - 48.1 MB",
              "format": "image/tiff"
            }
          ],
          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/canvas/p4/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>Now I am willing &amp; ready to surrender<lb/> all real &amp; personal interest I own\n                in the<lb/> synagogue &amp; unite with the other society<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">provided</hi>—there shall be no overreacting<lb/> and departure\n                from the limits of enlight<lb/>-ened orthodoxy.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am in favor of a<lb/> preacher of enlightened views—a school-<lb/>\n                of doing away with certain customs<lb/> (mere forms)—of repetition of prayers—<lb/>\n                and of other sensible modifications,<lb/> but I decline to reject the belief in<lb/>\n                a personal messiah &amp; the resurrection<lb/> of the body. These I hold as\n                funda<lb/>-mental principles of our faith that<lb/> cannot be abolished or\n                abandoned.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now with reference to Pews—<lb/> I believe neither the Pentateuch\n                nor Prophets speak<lb/> advisedly on this point—the only reason<lb/> for the\n                    <sic>seperation</sic> of the sexes I have<lb/> ever heard advanced &amp; have\n                entertained<lb/> myself have been with reference to cleanli<lb/>-ness &amp; the\n                reverse at certain periods<lb/> in the other sex. Understand me<lb/> though—that\n                while I say this to you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p33776f85/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
